<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4371&amp;p=8093#p8093"><![CDATA[
Your code looks like it does what you want. You're only missing the elements the script tries to hook in to. Try adding this:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;div id=status&gt;&lt;/div&gt;<br />&lt;div id=state&gt;&lt;/div&gt;<br />&lt;div id=log&gt;&lt;/div&gt;<br /></code></dd></dl><br />Also, I think the online and offline events get fired on window, not body, so you should do window.addEventListener. (body.ononline or &lt;body ononline=&quot;&quot;&gt; handlers actually add a listener on window.)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Thu Sep 20, 2012 8:33 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
